  "title": "CONSTRUCTION MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Project Planning: Construction managers develop project plans, defining scope, objectives, and deliverables. They create schedules, establish timelines, and set milestones to ensure efficient project progression.</p><p></p><p>Resource Management: They handle resource allocation, including labor, equipment, and materials, ensuring effective utilization and timely delivery to meet project milestones.</p><p></p><p>Budget Management: Construction managers prepare and oversee project budgets, tracking expenses to ensure projects stay within financial constraints. They collaborate with stakeholders to address cost-related issues and seek cost-saving opportunities.</p><p></p><p>Risk Management: They identify potential risks and uncertainties, conducting assessments and developing mitigation strategies to ensure compliance with safety regulations and building codes.</p><p></p><p>On-Site Supervision: Construction managers monitor and supervise on-site activities, ensuring that construction work is carried out safely and efficiently. They coordinate with various stakeholders, including clients, architects, engineers, and contractors.</p><p></p>",
